  "title": "Sales Admin (4 months Temp)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Highlights:</strong></p><ul><li>Salary: $12/hour</li><li>Transport Allowance: $200/month</li><li>Duration: Feb – May 2026 (4months contract)</li><li>Working Days: Monday to Friday</li><li>Working Hours: 8:30 AM – 5:30 PM</li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Process customer orders, acknowledge POs, update order status, delivery schedules, and maintain accuracy in MS/MRP systems.</li><li>Liaise with customers on order updates, delivery timelines, stock availability, and handle enquiries or complaints professionally.</li><li>Prepare shipping documents and invoices, manage delivery changes, support freight coordination and basic customs documentation.</li><li>Coordinate with Production, Planning, Purchasing, Warehouse, QA, and Sales to ensure timely and accurate order fulfilment.</li><li>Support sales administration, AR follow-ups, monthly reporting, stock counts, reconciliation, and other assigned admin duties.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>No experience required (training will be provided)</li><li>Comfortable with order processing, documentation and coordination work</li><li>Proficient in basic Microsoft Office (e.g., Excel, Word) will be an advantage</li><li>Able to work in a fast-paced environment and meet timelines</li></ul><p>Interested candidate may send your full resume to <strong>6990 0458 (WhatsApp – Yong Jia Wen)</strong> and only shortlisted candidate will be notified.</p><p>By submitting your personal data and/or resume, you give consent to collection, use and disclosure of your personal data and/or resume by the company (or its agent) for the purpose of the processing and administration by the company relating to this job application.</p><p>https://www.mci.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/MCI-Job-Applicant-Data-Protection-Notice.pdf</p><p><strong>Yong Jia Wen</strong><br /><strong>Registration Number: R25146805</strong><br /><strong>EA License No: 13C6730 (MCI Consulting Pte Ltd)</strong></p>",
